title: Florida sweeps Tennessee in volleyball
text:
Florida sweeps Tennessee in volleyball News Sentinel staff 9:55 PM, Oct 14, 2015 Power T logo Copyright 2015 Journal Media Group. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed. Show Caption Previous Next 
Florida won the first two sets and Tennessee couldn't swing the momentum in the third as the Vols fell 25-19, 25-11, 25-23 in a volleyball match on Wednesday at Thompson-Boling Arena. 
The Vols (17-5, 3-4 SEC) entered the match in search of their first back-to-back wins over top-25 teams since 2012. 
"We put ourselves in a position to win the first and third set, but unfortunately, we made some unforced errors we had not been making in transition," Tennessee coach Rob Patrick said in a school release. "That hurt us a little in terms of being able to close out the third set and being able to push through in the first set." 
After Florida won a lopsided second set, Tennessee led the third set 22-18 after a kill by Kendra Turner and an error by Florida. 
But the Gators (12-4, 4-3) regained momentum to close out the match on a 7-1 run. 
Sophomore Kanisha Jimenez led Tennessee with nine kills and added five digs. Raina Hembry had six kills and four blocks. 
Tennessee continues its three-match homestand when it plays South Carolina on Sunday at 1:30 p.m. 
Men's Tennis: Tennessee is playing host to the USTA/ITA Men's Ohio Valley Regional Championships starting Thursday and runs through Monday. 
Both the Goodfriend Tennis Center on campus and the Knoxville Racquet Club will be used Thursday through Saturday. All action will be at Goodfriend beginning Sunday. 
The finals are Monday. 
Admission is free. Fans are directed to park in the N-7 garage where Andy Holt and Volunteer Boulevard meet. For Monday's finals, the S-17 lot adjacent to Goodfriend will be available.
